On March 3, Brent crude was trading at approximately $84 per barrel — a 22% spike that felt dramatic at the time. By the evening of March 8, Brent briefly touched **$126 per barrel** before closing around $99. WTI posted its biggest weekly gain in recorded history at 35.6%. The chart in Part B showing a $84 peak on March 3 understates the current situation by roughly 50%.

